article.headline: Lipscomb 70, Samford 65
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- LaKory Daniels scored five points in overtime to help Lipscomb beat visiting Samford 70-65 Monday night. Lipscomb (2-5) was led by Eddie Ard and Brandon Brown with 17 points each. Samford (2-3) got 20 points from Joe Ross Merritt, but was outscored 13-8 in overtime. Lipscomb led the entire overtime, with Daniels hitting a 3-point jumper to break a 57-all tie with 4:29 left. Daniels made two free throws with nine seconds left to push the Bisons' lead to 70-63. Samford did not score for a three-minute stretch during overtime. Lipscomb hit 18-of-24 free throws to Samford's 12-of-20.
